---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Trust, Security, and Responsible Use"
  description="How we handle data, accuracy, and quality control. Your team reviews everything before it goes out."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Trust and security</p>
      <h1>Your team stays in control of what goes out.</h1>
      <p>
        AI helps speed things up, but your team still reviews anything
        important before it's sent. We also cover what shouldn't be shared
        with public tools, where accuracy matters most, and how to keep tone
        and standards consistent.
      </p>
      <a class="button" href="/contact/">Book a free call</a>
    </div>
    <aside class="panel panel-pad">
      <h2>This is part of the training, not an afterthought.</h2>
      <p class="lead">Especially important for legal, accounting, healthcare, and property teams.</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid grid-3">
      {[
        ["Data handling", "We show teams what shouldn't go into public tools and how to work from safe summaries instead."],
        ["Accuracy", "AI can sound confident when it's wrong. Everything gets checked by your team before it's used."],
        ["Professional judgment", "Legal, tax, clinical, valuation, and compliance decisions stay with the people qualified to make them."],
        ["Client communication", "AI can help put together a draft. Your team checks the tone, the facts, and the commitments before it goes out."],
        ["Internal processes", "AI can turn messy notes into something structured, but the people who own the process approve the final version."],
        ["Tool choice", "The session works with whatever tools your team is already allowed to use. We're not selling software."],
      ].map(([title, body]) => (
        <article class="card">
          <h3>{title}</h3>
          <p>{body}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-tight">
    <div class="panel panel-pad">
      <p class="eyebrow">Where the boundaries are</p>
      <h2>This is about getting work done faster, not replacing anyone's expertise.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Healthcare examples focus on admin and patient communication, not
        clinical decisions. Legal examples focus on preparation, not advice.
        Accounting examples focus on reporting and research, not sign-off.
        Property examples keep valuations and regulated statements with the
        people qualified to make them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
